    "def get_df(table_name:str) -> pd.DataFrame: \n",
    "    conn = get_connector() \n",
    "    \n",
    "    qry = f'select * from {table_name}' \n",
    "    df = pd.read_sql(qry, conn)\n",
    "    conn.close()\n",
    "\n",

    "    # cat_cols = ['first_utm_campaign', 'first_utm_medium', 'first_device_category', 'lf_how_did_you_hear', 'lf_industry', 'has_converted']\n",

    "def make_dataset_backup():\n",
    "    date_suffix = datetime.today().date().strftime('%Y%m%d')\n",
    "    table_name = f'eva.model.leads_score_{date_suffix}'\n",
    "    \n",
    "    conn = get_connector() \n",
    "    \n",
    "    print('Step: Drop table if exists.')\n",
    "\n",
    "    rm_existing_table = f'drop table if exists {table_name};'\n",
    "    conn.cursor().execute(rm_existing_table)\n",
    "    conn.commit()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print('Completed.')\n",
    "\n",
    "    print('Step: Loading new table.')\n",
    "\n",
    "    create_clause = f'''\n",
    "    create table if not exists {table_name}\n",
    "    as \n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    qry = create_clause + open('leads_to_conversion.sql', 'r').read()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    conn.cursor().execute(qry)\n",
    "    conn.commit()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print('Completed.')\n",
    "\n",
    "    qry = f'select * from {table_name}' \n",
    "    df = pd.read_sql(qry+' limit 10', conn)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if not df.empty:\n",
    "        print(f'table name: {table_name}')\n",
    "        return table_name\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print('No data was queried. Returning empty DF')\n",
    "        return None\n"
   ]

    "def trim_outliers(df:pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame: \n",
    "    trim_cols = ['cummul_duration']\n",
    "\n",
    "# trimmed the top and tail 1 % \n",
    "    df = df[(np.abs(stats.zscore(df[trim_cols])) < 3).all(axis=1)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return df "
   ]

    "def update_mrk_source(df:pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Update marketing_source that has count less than 20 to `others` so that the data is model dense.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    df = df.copy()\n",
    "    cnter = df['mkt_source'].value_counts()\n",
    "    keys = cnter[cnter.values<20].index.tolist()\n",
    "    df['mkt_source'] = df['mkt_source'].replace(dict(zip(keys, ['others']*len(keys))))\n",
    "    return df "
   ]
